docs.snippet: DULUTH, Minn., July 27 (AP) --Mrs. Marlene Bauer Hagge exploded a burst of birdies on the finishing holes today to take a one-stroke lead over Louise Suggs at the halfway point of the Women's National Open Golf tournament.

docs.snippet: DULUTH, Minn., July 28-- Barbara McIntire, an amateur from Toledo, carded a threeunder-par 71 today to tie Mrs. Kathy Cornelius at 302 and force an eighteen-hole play-off for the women's National Open golf championship.
